# What belongs in a bundle

For **workspace-shaped code** — not data, not infra.

| Asset | In a bundle? |
|---|---|
| Jobs · pipelines · notebooks | ✅ |
| Python files / wheels · ML models | ✅ |
| Volumes + schemas it creates · dashboards | ✅ |
| Raw data files | ❌ not a data tool |
| UC **catalogs** themselves | ❌ out of band, referenced |
| Service principals / IAM roles | ❌ cloud / IdP managed |
| Secret **values** | ❌ only scope **references** |

- **Rule:** code → bundle; infra (catalogs, principals) + data → Terraform / IaC / pipelines
- **Why:** different lifecycles — deploy a bundle daily; create a catalog **once**. Bundle **references** infra by name.
